release: 3.1.0

write_timezone: Always truncate before writing

In #93 it was reported that previous timezones were still ending up in
/etc/timezone. This sounded improbable since everything was working for
me, but then of course I checked myself and saw:

    % cat /etc/timezone
    Europe/Paris

    rk
    es

It seems like glibc only cares up to the first newline, so I never
noticed that we're not truncating properly, but we should certainly be
truncating here.

Fixes #93.

file: safe_canonicalise_path: Use .canonicalize()

api: Show errors as debug

For example, wtz returns 404s:

    % target/debug/tzupdate -p -i 1.1.1.1
    [2023-05-26T22:17:00Z ERROR tzupdate::http] https://worldtimeapi.org/api/ip/1.1.1.1: status code 404
    [...]

We already tell people to run with debug mode for errors, so don't log
these so loudly either.
